    "body" : "I just want to point out that <a href=\"https://intellij-support.jetbrains.com/hc/en-us/articles/206827587-How-to-manage-projects-under-Version-Control-Systems\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">intellij-support.jetbrains.com/hc/en-us/articles/&hellip;</a> is the official answer to what should be in <code>.gitignore</code>, and this workaround goes against this. You lose some ability to share project properties to all developers, such as inspections/lint settings that we use to prevent some standard bad-practices before even getting to code review. You can just add <code>&#47;.idea&#47;misc.xml</code> to the <code>.gitignore</code> file to solve this."
