      "body" : "@BarryStaes, thanks for feedback. I did not find perfect solution for this issue (other solutions didn&#39;t work) and this one works for me and few other people. Note that this is not completely ignoring the files only hiding the fact they have changed. Since these files can often and randomly change it allows to filter them up when doing git commands. You can still commit them whenever you want."
