    "body" : "<p>It seems the file <a href=\"https://intellij-support.jetbrains.com/hc/en-us/articles/206544839-How-to-manage-projects-under-Version-Control-Systems\" rel=\"noreferrer\">should be stored under version control</a>. I would propose to keep it in git, but ignore all local changes:</p>\n\n<pre><code>git update-index --assume-unchanged .idea/misc.xml\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>When switching branches there might be conflict in these files. Then you could use following <em>imlreset</em> script to reset the files:</p>\n\n<pre><code>#!/bin/bash                                                                     \nwhile read f                                                                    \ndo                                                                              \n  [ -f $f ] &amp;&amp; git checkout $f                                                    \ndone &lt;&lt;!                                                                        \napp/app.iml                                                           \nwear/wear.iml                                                                   \n!\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Create similar script for ignoring these files if you do it often.</p>\n"
